VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-812b-8548-e3f0fbab4556', 'Apple Cider Donut Waffle Bites', 'üßá', NULL, 'Breakfast', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/reel/CyTLkpcu5Jl/?igshid=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["2 cups all-purpose flour","4 tsp baking powder","1/2 tsp salt","1 tsp apple pie spice","1/2 tsp cinnamon","1 tbsp brown or coconut sugar","1 cup buttermilk (or 1 cup milk + 1 tbsp vinegar mixed together)","1 cup apple cider","6 tbsp avocado oil OR coconut oil (melted) OR butter (melted)","1 egg","1/3 cup granulated sugar","1 tsp cinnamon","Optional: 1/4 tsp nutmeg"]', 'Preheat waffle iron. In a small bowl, mix together the ingredients for the for spiced sugar. Set aside. In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, salt, apple pie spice, and cinnamon. In a separate large bowl, whisk together the brown or coconut sugar, buttermilk, apple cider, avocado oil, and egg. Add the dry ingredients into the wet, and mix until well combined (it''s okay if the batter is a little clumpy). Spray the waffle iron with nonstick cooking spray. Add enough batter to fill each waffle section. Cook the waffles until golden brown. Once done, immediately roll in the spiced sugar to coat. Repeat with the remaining batter and coating. Serve warm with maple syrup. Enjoy!', 1760731829780, 1760731829780, 0);
