VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-811b-8ae5-c0cecea58397', 'Quick', 'üçú', NULL, 'Dinner', NULL, 'https://tiffycooks.com/spicy-garlic-noodles-10-minutes-only/', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["2 lbs Chicken","Sourdough Ramen Noodles","1-2 Shallots, diced","1.5-2 tbsp Homemade Chilli Oil","2 tbsp Soy Sauce","3 tbsp Black Vinegar","1 tbsp Crushed Red Chilli Flakes","1 tbsp Sesame Seeds","6-8 cloves Garlic, minced","1/4 Cup Cilantro, chopped","Juice of 1-2 Limes","4 tbsp Oil","1 tsp Sichuan Peppercorn","1/2 Cup Fresh Orange Juice","1 Cup Soy Sauce","2 Tbsp Rice Vinegar","1/4 Cup Fish Sauce","2 tsp Garlic Powder","2 tsp Ginger Powder","1 tsp Sesame Oil (optional)"]', 'Marinate the chicken in the all-purpose stir fry sauce for a few hours up to 24 hours in advance. In a bowl, add in 2 tbsp of Soy sauce, 3 tbsp of Black Vinegar, 1.5-2 tbsp of Homemade Chilli Oil, Crushed Red Chilli Flakes, Sesame Seeds, diced shallots. Mince the garlic and set aside in another small bowl for now. Chop up your cilantro and lime juice and place in another separate small bowl (you will add this in to the sauce at the end). First cook the chicken in the marinade until done. While the chicken is cooking heat up your water that you will cook the noodles in (make sure to salt your water). Once the chicken is done, heat 4 tbsp of oil and once the oil is hot add in 1 tsp of Sichuan Peppercorn for a few minutes. Next place a spoon with the minced garlic in the first bowl you made with the soy sauce, black vinegar, etc. Pour the hot oil over the garlic and make sure to strain the oil so the peppercorn doesn''t go in. Let the oil sizzle and mix. Then add in the cilantro and lime juice to the sauce. Cook the sourdough noodles in the boiling water for 90 seconds or until soft and chewy (this could take a little longer). Drain the noodles and then add the sauce into the noodles. Serve with the chicken. You can also add in cucumber, green onion, fried egg, and/or cilantro.', 1760731829780, 1760731829780, 0);
