VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-816a-9626-daa0e197c01c', 'Chicken Enchilada Empanadas', 'ü•ü', NULL, 'Dinner', NULL, NULL, 'rb_3', '108', NULL, 0, '["15-ounce can tomato sauce","¬Ω cup chicken stock","1 tablespoon chili powder","2 teaspoons paprika","2 teaspoons granulated garlic","1 teaspoon smoked paprika","1 teaspoon powdered onion","1 teaspoon ground coriander","Salt to taste","1 pound chicken breast, cut into small cubes","4 ounces goat cheese (optional)","1 egg yolk","1 tablespoon water"]', '1 Preheat oven to 400¬∞F. Lightly grease a sheet pan.
2 In a sauce pot combine tomato sauce, chicken stock, and spices. Add cubed chicken breast and bring to a simmer. Continue to simmer for 20 minutes.
3 Meanwhile, prepare the dough. Combine flour and salt in a large bowl. Add water to another large bowl and sprinkle in gelatin. Let sit for 1 minute. Whisk in oil and eggs. Whisk wet ingredients into dry, and knead until a dough has formed.
4 Divide the dough into 10 uniform balls. Split each ball in half. Use your hands to press the dough into very thin discs. Place one disc on the sheet pan, top with 3 tablespoons of enchilada filling and goat cheese (if using). Top with another dough disc. Roll the sides of the dough up around the filling and press to create a seal. Continue until all the dough has been used.
5 Use a pastry brush to lightly brush the empanadas with egg wash.
6 Bake until golden brown, about 28 to 30 minutes.', 1760731829780, 1760731829780, 0);
