VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-815d-bbe3-faf2db31484e', 'Beef & Cabbage Stir-Fry with Garlic, Ginger, and Fermented Tamari', 'üêÑ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["1/2 lb grass-fed ground beef or thinly sliced steak","1/2 head green or napa cabbage, thinly sliced","2 cloves garlic, minced","1 tbsp fresh ginger, minced or grated","1‚Äì2 tbsp fermented tamari (gluten-free soy sauce alternative)","1 tbsp beef tallow or ghee","Optional: chopped scallions, sesame seeds, or a dash of apple cider vinegar"]', '1. Prep Ingredients: Slice cabbage thinly. Mince garlic and ginger. 2. Cook Beef: Heat tallow or ghee in a large skillet over medium heat. Add ground beef or sliced steak and cook until browned. Set aside if you want to stir-fry veggies separately for more control. 3. Saut√© Aromatics: In the same pan, add a bit more fat if needed. Saut√© garlic and ginger for 30 seconds until fragrant. 4. Add Cabbage: Toss in the sliced cabbage. Stir-fry for about 5‚Äì7 minutes until tender but still vibrant. 5. Combine & Season: Add the cooked beef back in, pour over fermented tamari, and toss everything together. Cook for 1‚Äì2 more minutes. 6. Serve: Garnish with scallions or sesame seeds. Serve alone or with a side of wild rice or cauliflower rice.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
