VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-81de-a889-e0e6cee0de43', 'BBQ Ribs', 'üêÆ', NULL, 'Dinner', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/reel/Cwcx32Cqj_s/?igshid=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["1 rack of baby back ribs","1 red onion","5 garlics","1 tsp fennel","2.5 cups of ketchup","1/2 cup of soy","1 cup of brown sugar","1 tsp of chili flakes"]', '1. Preheat over to 265 degrees F
2. Cook the diced onions in oil for 3-4 minutes.
3. Add in Garlic, Fennel, and Chili flakes and cook for another 2 minutes
4. Add in brown sugar and cook down till everything is emulsified
5. Add in Ketchup and Soy sauce and cook for another 2-3 minutes
6. Put the sauce all over the ribs. Make sure to get it on the bottom as well.
7. Cover the ribs with foil and make sure it''s tight. No air should get out.
8. Cook for about 1.5-2 hours depending on the thickness.
9. Take out the oven, remove the top cover and re-coat the ribs with the sauce.
10. Increase heat to 325 degrees F and place the ribs in for another 30 minutes
11. Take it out, let it sit and cool down for a few minutes an enjoy!', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
