VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-81a0-8384-fa24c2816359', 'Protein Waffles', 'üßá', NULL, 'Breakfast', NULL, NULL, 'rb_15', '36', NULL, 0, '["1 cup organic rolled oats","1 cup cottage cheese","4 large eggs","1 tsp. baking powder","2 tbsp. ground flax","1 tsp. ground cinnamon","2 tbsp. maple syrup","2 tbsp. coconut oil or butter"]', 'Place all the ingredients, except for the butter, in a high-powered blender or food processor and blend for 20-30 seconds, or until smooth. Preheat a waffle iron and lightly grease with the butter or coconut oil. Pour the batter onto the heated waffle iron until it covers most of the center''s surface area. Close the lid and allow to cook until golden brown. Remove from the waffle iron and repeat with the remaining batter. Store leftover waffles in an airtight container for up to 3 days or freeze for up to 3 months and reheat in a toaster, microwave, or back in the waffle iron. You can also make these into pancakes. Prepare the batter as directed and cook according to the directions for the buckwheat pancakes (pg 32).', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
