VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-8184-a9ce-fbedcc81166e', 'Citrus-Dill Garlic Chicken with Grilled Summer Veggies', 'üêî', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["1.5 lbs pasture-raised chicken thighs or breasts, boneless and skinless","Zest of 1 lemon","Juice of 2 lemons","2 tbsp fresh dill, finely chopped (or 2 tsp dried)","2 garlic cloves, minced","2 tbsp olive oil","¬Ω tsp sea salt","Freshly ground black pepper, to taste","2 zucchinis, sliced into thick coins or long spears","1 red onion, cut into thick wedges","1 red bell pepper, sliced into large chunks","1 bunch of asparagus, sliced into large chunks","1 tbsp olive oil","Sea salt + black pepper","Optional: additional lemon juice or zest for garnish"]', '1. Marinate the Chicken: In a large bowl or zip-top bag, mix together lemon juice, zest, dill, garlic, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Add the chicken and coat well. Marinate in the fridge for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
2. Prep the Veggies: Toss all vegetables in olive oil, salt, and pepper. Let them sit while the grill heats up.
3. Grill the Chicken: Preheat the grill to medium-high heat. Remove chicken from marinade and place on grill. Cook for: Thighs: ~6‚Äì7 minutes per side, Breasts: ~5‚Äì6 minutes per side. Check that internal temp reaches 165¬∞F (74¬∞C).
4. Grill the Veggies: While the chicken cooks, place veggies on the grill (you can use a grill basket if needed). Grill for 3‚Äì5 minutes per side until tender with nice char marks.
5. Serve: Plate the grilled chicken with the veggies. Garnish with extra fresh dill, lemon zest, or a squeeze of lemon juice if desired.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
