VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-810a-b3ae-ccce15a656cf', 'Pie crust', 'ü•ß', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'rb_18', '402', NULL, 0, '["1 cup cassava flour","3 tablespoons arrowroot powder","¬º to ¬Ω teaspoon salt","¬Ω cup palm shortening or Ghee (393)","1 egg","3 to 4 tablespoons cold water"]', 'In a food processor, add the cassava flour, arrowroot powder, and salt. Pulse to combine. Add the palm shortening or ghee and pulse until incorporated and the mixture looks like coarse crumbs. Add the egg and pulse until combined. Add the water a tablespoon at a time until the dough starts to come together and is not too sticky. Dust your hands with cassava flour and form the dough into a ball. Place it on a flat, floured surface or a piece of parchment paper. Dust the dough with more cassava flour, flatten the dough into a disc, and place another piece of parchment paper on top. Roll the dough into a circle about ¬º-inch thick. Transfer the dough to a pie plate, press it into place, and crimp the edges. Poke the bottom a few times with a fork. Fill and bake the crust as indicated in the pie recipe. To pre-bake the crust for use in recipes that do not require further baking, bake in a 350 degree oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown. Make it Ahead: If you are not using the dough right away, it can be wrapped in plastic wrap and stored in the refrigerator for a few days.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
