VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-8183-8828-deca6ea1f2b8', 'Middle Eastern Chicken & Rice Bowl', 'üêî', NULL, 'Dinner', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/reel/C0c9P0hOYpk/?igshid=ZWQ3ODFjY2VlOQ==', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["2 lbs chicken thighs","1.5 tbsp EVOO","1 tbsp smoked paprika","1 tbsp garlic powder","1 tbsp thyme","1/2 tbsp chili flakes","1/2 tsp cumin","1/4 tsp cinnamon","salt & pepper","2 tbsp yogurt","1/4 cup yogurt for dressing","juice of 2 lemons (1 for chicken, 1 for salad)","1 red onion","handful cherry tomatoes","parsley","2 tbsp sumac","1/4 cup pickle juice","2 dill pickles","3 tbsp mayo","2 tbsp fresh dill","rice"]', '1. Add 2 lbs chicken thighs to a bowl. Drizzle with 1.5 tbsp EVOO and season with 1 tbsp smoked paprika, 1 tbsp garlic powder, 1 tbsp thyme, 1/2 tbsp chili flakes, 1/2 tsp cumin, 1/4 tsp cinnamon, salt & pepper, 2 tbsp plain yogurt, & juice of 1 lemon. Mix well, then ideally marinate for 4-6 hrs, but can make immediately.
2. Bring a pan to medium heat, add 1 tbsp oil, add chicken (brought to room temp), and cook through on medium heat. Cook 4 mins on each side, then 1-2 minutes on each side again. Total time about 10-12 mins depending on thickness.
3. Make salad by thinly slicing 1 large red onion, small handful cherry tomatoes, large handful fresh flat parsley. Add to bowl, sprinkle with 2-3 pinches salt, 2 tbsp sumac, & juice of 1 large lemon. Mix well and let sit 10 mins, stirring couple times.
4. Make white sauce by mixing 1/4 cup plain yogurt, 3 tbsp mayo, 1/8 to 1/4 cup pickle juice, 2 tbsp fresh dill, small pinch salt, & lots fresh cracked pepper. Mix well, taste, & adjust.
5. Get base ready. Use low carb rice or regular rice.
6. When rice is cooked, add serving to bowl, some chicken, pile high with salad, sliced Persian cucumbers, fresh herbs, and drizzle with white sauce.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
