VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-8144-8513-f9c8a2e6e49c', 'Grilled Kofta Kebabs', 'üêÆ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["1 lb ground beef (80‚Äì85% lean)","¬Ω medium onion, finely grated (about ¬º cup, with juice)","2‚Äì3 garlic cloves, minced","2 tbsp fresh parsley, finely chopped","1 tbsp fresh mint, finely chopped (or 1 tsp dried mint)","1 tsp ground cumin","1 tsp ground coriander","¬Ω tsp ground cinnamon","¬æ tsp sea salt","¬Ω tsp black pepper","Pinch of chili flakes for heat (optional)","1 tbsp olive oil (optional, if mixture is too lean/dry)","Bamboo or metal skewers"]', '1. Prepare the meat mixture: In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, grated onion (with juice), garlic, herbs, and spices. Mix gently with your hands or a fork until everything is well distributed. Don''t overmix or it may become tough.
2. Form the kebabs: Divide the mixture into 6‚Äì8 portions. With damp hands, shape each portion into a long oval or log shape around a skewer (about 5‚Äì6 inches long). If using wooden skewers, soak them in water for at least 30 minutes beforehand to prevent burning.
3. Chill (optional but helpful): Place formed skewers on a plate and refrigerate for 15‚Äì30 minutes to help them hold their shape on the grill.
4. Grill: Preheat grill to medium-high. Oil the grill grates or brush kebabs lightly with oil to prevent sticking. Grill for about 3‚Äì5 minutes per side, rotating to brown all sides, until cooked through and nicely charred.
5. Serve: Great with cucumber yogurt sauce (tzatziki), grilled veggies, or wrapped in lettuce or gluten-free flatbread. A side of lemony cucumber salad or grilled zucchini is perfect!', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
