VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-81e9-883d-d732b013b2ec', 'Beef & Cabbage Hash ', 'üêÑ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["1 lb grass-fed ground beef or turkey","2 tbsp finely chopped fresh oregano","¬Ω tsp sea salt","2 tbsp grass-fed butter or ghee","2 cups green cabbage, finely sliced","1 cup Brussels sprouts, shredded","1 large onion, coarsely chopped","4 cloves garlic, minced","¬Ω tsp ground coriander","¬Ω tsp ground ginger","2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley or cilantro (optional, for topping)"]', '1. In a medium skillet over medium-high heat, cook the beef, oregano, coriander, and ¬º tsp of salt for about 10 minutes or until fully browned. Remove from pan and set aside.
2. Wipe out the skillet and return it to the heat. Melt the butter, then add the onion and Brussels sprouts. Saut√© for 5 minutes.
3. Add the cabbage, garlic, ginger, lemon zest, remaining ¬º tsp salt, and a splash of water if needed to deglaze. Stir frequently and cook for another 5‚Äì6 minutes until everything is soft and slightly golden.
4. Stir in the beef and warm through for 1‚Äì2 minutes. Top with parsley or cilantro and serve.
