VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-811a-8edf-ce47677b9a73', 'Lactation Granola Bars', 'üåæ', '["Postpartum"]', 'Snack', NULL, NULL, 'rb_15', '85', NULL, 0, '["2 cups organic old-fashioned rolled oats","2 tbsp. Debittered brewer''s yeast","‚Öì cup ground flax","1 cup unsweetened shredded coconut","1 cup slivered almonds","1 tsp. Chia seeds","6 pitted dates, chopped","¬º cup coconut sugar or panela sugar","‚Öî cup maple syrup","3 tbsp. Coconut oil or butter","1 ¬Ω tsp. Pure vanilla extract","¬º tsp. Salt","¬º cup semisweet chocolate chips or dried fruit"]', 'Preheat oven to 325¬∞. Combine the oats, brewers yeast, ground flax, coconut (if using), and almonds on an ungreased cookie sheet. Spread out evenly and bake for 10 minutes, or until lightly toasted. Remove from the oven. Lower the temperature to 300¬∞. Line an 8" square baking pan with parchment paper and set aside. In a large bowl, add the toasted ingredients, chia seeds, dates, and sugar. In a small saucepan, bring the maple syrup, coconut oil or butter, vanilla, and salt to a low boil and simmer for 2 minutes. Pour over the dry ingredients until and mix until fully incorporated. Quickly stir in the chocolate chips and pour into a prepared baking pan, spreading out evenly. Use a piece of wax paper to press down firmly to flatten. Bake for 25-30 minutes at 300¬∞, or until the edges are golden brown. Remove from the oven and allow to cool for 1 hour before removing from the pan to cut. Cut into twelve bars and store in an airtight container for up to 2 weeks.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
