VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-81e9-8e30-ddd60cb3cd14', 'Instant Pot Golden Chicken & Root Stew', 'üêî', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'rb_27', NULL, NULL, 0, '["1.5‚Äì2 lbs pasture-raised chicken thighs or drumsticks, bone-in skin-on (or boneless if you prefer)","1 tbsp olive oil or animal fat (like beef tallow or chicken schmaltz)","4 cloves garlic, minced","1 small yellow onion, chopped (omit if sensitive)","3 carrots, peeled and chopped","2 parsnips or 1 sweet potato, peeled and chopped","2 ribs celery, sliced","1 small rutabaga or 1 cup chopped butternut squash","1 inch piece fresh ginger, grated or sliced","1 tsp turmeric powder or 1 inch fresh turmeric root, grated","1/2 tsp cinnamon","1 tsp sea salt, or to taste","Freshly ground black pepper, optional","1 tbsp apple cider vinegar","4‚Äì5 cups filtered water or homemade bone broth (no tomato)","Optional: a handful of chopped greens (like kale or chard) added in the last 30 mins","Optional: fresh herbs like parsley or dill to garnish"]', '**Instructions for Instant Pot**
1. Saut√© (optional but adds flavor)
    - Set Instant Pot to Saut√© mode.
    - Add 1 tbsp olive oil or animal fat.
    - Sear chicken 2‚Äì3 minutes per side until lightly browned. Remove and set aside.
2. Saut√© aromatics
    - In the same pot, add onion (if using), garlic, ginger, and a pinch of salt. Saut√© 2‚Äì3 minutes until fragrant.
    - Press Cancel.
3. Deglaze
    - Pour in a splash of broth or water and use a wooden spoon to scrape any browned bits from the bottom.
4. Add all ingredients
    - Layer in the root veggies, spices (turmeric, cinnamon, salt), apple cider vinegar, and remaining broth or water (about 4 cups).
    - Place seared chicken on top.
5. Pressure Cook
    - Lock the lid, set valve to Sealing.
    - Press Manual or Pressure Cook and set time for 15 minutes on High Pressure.
6. Natural Release
    - Let pressure release naturally for 10‚Äì15 minutes, then release the rest manually.
7. Final Touches
    - Remove chicken, shred or chop, and return to the pot.
    - (Optional) Stir in a handful of chopped greens and let them wilt with the residual heat.
    - Add fresh herbs or a drizzle of flax/olive oil for an extra nutrient boost.
**‚úÖ Notes:**
- This recipe works great with fresh meat for lower histamine content.
- Store leftovers in glass containers and reheat gently (avoid long refrigeration if histamine-sensitive ‚Äî freeze if needed).
- For added gut support, stir in 1 tbsp collagen or gelatin powder before serving.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
