VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-8134-9d3d-e5de15f5e785', 'Butternut Squash Bake (ChatGPT)', 'ü•í', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["1 large butternut squash (about 2¬Ω‚Äì3 lbs), peeled, seeded, and cut into 1-inch cubes","2 tablespoons ghee or butter (melted)","1 tablespoon olive oil (optional for roasting)","1 ¬Ω teaspoons sea salt","¬Ω teaspoon black pepper","1 tablespoon chopped fresh sage (or ¬Ω teaspoon dried)","1 medium yellow onion, thinly sliced","1‚Äì2 teaspoons maple syrup (optional, for a subtle sweetness)","¬º cup grated Parmesan cheese or 2 tablespoons nutritional yeast (for dairy-free option)","2 slices cooked bacon, crumbled (optional)","Extra sage leaves crisped in butter for garnish (optional)"]', '1. Preheat oven to 400¬∞F (200¬∞C). Line a large baking dish (9x13) or sheet pan with parchment paper. 2. Prepare the squash: Toss cubed butternut squash with melted ghee, olive oil (if using), salt, pepper, and chopped sage until evenly coated. 3. Roast: Spread squash in a single layer and roast for 25‚Äì30 minutes, tossing halfway through, until golden and tender. 4. Caramelize the onions (while squash roasts): Heat 1 teaspoon ghee in a skillet over medium heat. Add sliced onions and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring often, for about 15 minutes until soft and golden brown. (Optional) Add a splash of water or a touch of maple syrup at the end to deepen the caramelization. 5. Assemble and bake: Once squash is tender, transfer to a baking dish if not already in one. Top with caramelized onions and Parmesan (or nutritional yeast). Return to oven for another 10 minutes until cheese melts and edges are golden. 6. Garnish and serve: Sprinkle with crispy bacon or sage leaves if desired. Serve warm.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
