VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-814c-b808-f2c6be01a391', 'One Pot Taco Soup', 'üç≤', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["1 lb thawed ground beef","1 quart chicken stock","Handful garlic cloves","28 oz diced tomatoes","30 oz black beans","30 oz corn","15 oz pinto beans","15 oz kidney beans","1 spoonful tomato paste","3 tbsp butter","Salt to taste","2 tsp smoked paprika (or to taste)","2 tsp cumin (or to taste)"]', 'Chop garlic and set aside. Warm pot on stove and add butter. Let melt. Add garlic and saut√© on low-medium heat until fragrant. Add ground beef (I add salt here too) and cook together with butter and garlic until done. Add spoonful of tomato paste. Mix in. Add chicken stock, then beans, corn, and diced tomatoes (I add a whole can, liquid and all). Add cumin, smoked paprika, and salt. Gently stir until combined. Add any additional cumin, paprika, or salt to taste as needed (I like a strong flavor). Set stove on low heat, cover, and let simmer until ready to serve. I like find the longer I give it the better it tastes, 2-3 hours is what I aim for. Top with cilantro, lime, hot sauce, sour cream, cheese, chips, olives, etc.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
