VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-8117-bd1c-d1db8cbe815b', 'ONE PAN ROAST with chipotle lime sauce', 'üêÆ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["2.5lbs chuck roast","Salt and fresh pepper","1/2 tbsp smoked paprika per side","1/2 tbsp thyme per side","12oz beef broth","6-8 cloves garlic","3 bay leaves","4 TBSP sour cream or thick greek yogurt","1-2 chipotle adobo peppers from the can","1 tablespoon adobo sauce from the can","Juice of 1 small lime"]', '1. Preheat your oven to 350F.
2. Start with 2.5lbs chuck roast and add it to an oven safe dish.
3. Season both sides of beef with a couple pinches salt & fresh pepper. Season each side with 1/2 tbsp smoked paprika & 1/2tbsp Thyme. Rub it in well to make sure its all covered.
4. Pour in 12oz beef broth and add 6-8 cloves garlic and 3 bay leaves.
5. Cover the roast with a lid, then put it in the oven at 350F for 2.5-3 hours. If yours is more than 2.5lb aim for about an hour per pound + 30 mins. So if its 3 lbs, 3.5 hrs, etc.
6. After the initial 2.5-3 hours, remove from the oven, shred the beef using two forks, mix well with the drippings, then put back in the oven at 375F for 45 mins to 1 hour. Shred again when you remove from the oven.
7. To make the sauce, in a small food processor combine sour cream or thick greek yogurt, chipotle adobo peppers, adobo sauce, salt, and lime juice. Give it a good pulse, then give it a taste and adjust.
8. Devour as is with the sauce, some avocado, fresh cilantro, or whatever toppings you want. Store for up to 5 days in the fridge.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
