VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-81a0-8084-ff5b60a9b40e', 'Tom Yum', 'üç≤', NULL, 'Dinner', NULL, NULL, 'rb_31', '58', NULL, 0, '["4 cups water","1 stick lemon grass","4 lime leaves (or 2 tbsp/25 mL lime juice)","1 inch galangal root (or ginger root)","2 fresh hot chilies","3 tbsp fish sauce","1 tsp sugar","1 1/2 tsp chili paste","2 oz button mushrooms","1 lb chicken","3 tbsp lime juice","3 tbsp fresh coriander leaves"]', '1. Heat 4 cups/1 L water in a soup pot to boiling.
2. Smash the lemon grass with the flat of a chef''s knife once, and then cut into 1-inch/2.5-cm pieces; tear the lime leaves into thirds; and slice the galangal into thin rounds. Reserve all three of these ingredients together.
3. Crush the fresh chilies and cut in half. Reserve separately.
4. When the water has boiled, add the reserved lemon grass/ galangal/lime leaves. Boil for 1 minute. Add fish sauce, sugar and chili paste. Boil for another 2 minutes. Add mushrooms and boil for 2 minutes. Add shrimps and lime juice (3 tbsp/ 45 mL plus the other 2 tbsp/25 mL if you haven''t used the lime leaves) and lower heat to medium-high. Cook for 2 minutes, just until the shrimps have turned white and springy. Transfer to a soup tureen, decorate with fresh coriander leaves and serve immediately.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
