VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-81cb-a304-de43ccbfece6', 'Mexican inspired Chuck Roast ', 'üêÆ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/reel/DBhF-JWSvJt/?igsh=MTFkYzN1Y3htaXBrNA==', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["chuck roast","Yellow onion","Salt","Pepper","Taco seasoning packet","Beef broth - 17 oz","Chipotle adobo","Garlic cloves","Avocados","Salsa","Cilantro"]', '1. Preheat oven to 325F.
2. Start with 3lbs beef chuck roast and add it to an oven safe dish. You''ll want one with a lid, or cover it for the first portion. Add 1 thinly sliced yellow onion at the base.
3. Season both sides of beef with 3-4 generous pinches salt, pepper, 1 packet of taco seasoning. Rub well on all sides.
4. Pour in 17oz of beef broth, 2 chipotle adobo peppers (from the can), and 4-5 minced garlic cloves.
5. Cover, then place in the oven at 325F for 4 hours. If yours is more than 3lb aim for about an hour per pound + 1 hour. So if its 2lbs go for 3 hours, or in this case 3 lbs, go for 4.
6. After 4hrs, remove the chuck roast from the oven, shred using two forks, mix well with the drippings, then put back in the oven at 400F for 30-40 mins. Shred again when you remove from the oven.
7. Devour as is with the sauce, some avocado, fresh cilantro, or whatever toppings you want. I served these inside lowcarb tortillas with mashed guac, fresh chopped cilantro, cheese, and topped with hot sauce.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
