VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-81b1-a85d-fc3a3ac7ed52', 'Short Rib Sandwich', 'üêÆ', NULL, 'Dinner', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/p/CwdSZA2IxxH/?hl=en', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["2.5 lbs short rib","Ciabatta bread","1 onion, chopped into chunks","Neutral oil","2 tbsp tomato paste","2 cups beef broth","1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce","4 garlic cloves, smashed","1/3 cup BBQ sauce","1 1/2 tbsp brown sugar","3 tsp kosher salt","1 tsp black pepper","1/2 tsp smoked paprika","1 tbsp chili powder","1 tsp garlic powder","1 tsp onion powder","1/2 tsp dry mustard","1 large carrot, shredded","1 1/2 cups green cabbage, shredded","1 1/2 cups purple cabbage, shredded","1/3 cup mayo","1 tbsp white vinegar","1/2 tbsp cider vinegar","1 tsp sugar","1/2 tsp celery seeds","1/2 tsp dried mustard","Salt & pepper to taste"]', 'Preheat oven to 325¬∞F. Mix together seasonings in a small bowl. Reserve 1/4 of the seasonings. Season all sides of the meat. In a Dutch oven over medium high heat, add 1 tbsp neutral oil and sear meat on all sides, remove, and set aside.
In the same pot, add tomato paste and cook for about 2 minutes. Add onions, beef broth, and BBQ sauce and mix. Add remaining 1/4 seasonings and garlic cloves, mix.
Add beef back into pot, cover, and place in preheated oven for 3 hours and 30 minutes. INSTAPOT OPTION: cook for 45 minutes on high pressure with a 10-15min natural release.
Remove meat and shred in a sheet pan. Broil meat for about 2-3 minutes, until slightly crispy.
For slaw: Add all ingredients to a bowl and mix.
For dipping sauce: Immersion blend the remaining liquids and onions in the Dutch oven.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
