VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-810a-b7f6-d19320999987', 'Garlic Parmesan Chicken Skewers', 'üêî', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/reel/DHeR4wLyovr/?igsh=MWxqaTh1NHV2NHFiaw==', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["1.5 lbs (680g) chicken thighs, boneless & skinless","3 tsp paprika","2 tsp garlic powder","2 tsp onion powder","2 tsp black pepper","1 tsp seasoning salt","1/2 lemon, juiced","2 tbsp yogurt","2 tbsp olive oil","1 stick butter (unsalted)","8 garlic cloves, minced","1/2 cup parmesan, grated","1 tbsp hot sauce (Frank''s)","2 tsp chili flakes","1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped"]', '1. If using wooden skewers, soak them in water for at least 15 minutes. 2. Cut chicken thighs into large bite-sized pieces. Mix all marinade ingredients together in a bowl with the chicken and toss to coat. Marinate for as long as desired - minimum one minute, or overnight for best flavor. 3. Preheat air fryer to 375¬∞F (190¬∞C). 4. In a large pan, melt butter and add minced garlic. Cook for two minutes over medium-low heat. Add parmesan, hot sauce, parsley and chili flakes. Mix for one minute then set aside. 5. Set aside 1/2 of the garlic butter, use the other 1/2 to baste chicken as it cooks. 6. Skewer chicken and cook for 7-8 minutes, baste with garlic butter and flip. Cook another 7-8 minutes, baste again and flip. 7. For extra crispy edges, increase temperature to 400¬∞F (205¬∞C) for the last 2-3 minutes. 8. Once cooked through, let rest for 5 minutes, then baste with reserved butter. Optionally finish with additional parmesan and fresh parsley.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
