VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-81bc-9af8-c80990de33cc', 'Herb-crusted chicken with roasted veggies ', 'üêî', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts","1/4 cup finely chopped fresh herbs (rosemary, thyme, and parsley)","2 tbsp almond flour","1/2 tsp salt and black pepper","1 tbsp olive oil","2 cups chopped root vegetables (carrots, sweet potato, parsnips)","1 tbsp olive oil","Salt and pepper to taste"]', '1. Preheat oven to 425¬∞F (220¬∞C).
2. On a large baking sheet, toss the chopped root vegetables with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Arrange them in a single layer.
3. In a shallow dish, combine the chopped fresh herbs, almond flour, salt, and pepper.
4. Brush the chicken breasts with a little olive oil, then press them into the herb mixture to coat both sides.
5. Place the herb-crusted chicken breasts on the baking sheet alongside the vegetables.
6. Roast for 20-25 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and the vegetables are tender and lightly caramelized.', 1760731829781, 1760731829781, 0);
