VALUES ('28fde7a2-c4fc-8106-b1d8-ed492fb77194', 'Lemony chicken stirfry', 'üêî', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '["1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breasts, sliced thin","1 tbsp olive oil","2 medium zucchini, julienned or spiralized","1 red onion, thinly sliced","1 bell pepper (any color), thinly sliced","Juice and zest of 1 lemon","2 tbsp olive oil","1 clove garlic, minced","1/2 tsp dried oregano","Salt and black pepper to taste"]', '1. In a small bowl, whisk together the lemon juice and zest, olive oil, garlic, oregano, salt, and pepper. Set aside.
2. Heat 1 tbsp of olive oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add the sliced chicken and cook until it''s cooked through and browned. Remove from the skillet and set aside.
3. Add the red onion and bell pepper to the skillet and stir-fry for 3-4 minutes until they begin to soften.
4. Add the zucchini to the skillet and stir-fry for 2-3 minutes until it''s tender-crisp.
